FBIS3-15862 "drsov047_a_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Nixon Continues Visit Despite Yeltsin Refusal To Meet LD0903155294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1522 GMT 9 Mar 94 LD0903155294 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow March 9 TASS -- Former U.S. President Richard Nixon will continue his unofficial visit to Moscow, Dimitri Simes, political scientist accompanying the ex-president, told reporters on Wednesday [9 February]. Thus he rejected media speculations that Nixon decided to cut short his visit after President Boris Yeltsin and some other top officials refused to meet him. The refusal came after Nixon's extensive contacts with opposition leaders including former Vice President Aleksandr Rutskoy amnestied last week.
